[32m+[m[32mBLUESTOCK MUTUAL FUND ANALYTICS PLATFORM[m
[32m+[m[32mBluestock Mutual Fund Analytics Platform[m
[32m+[m[32mCapstone Project Report[m
[32m+[m[32mSubmitted by:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Sricharan Medaboina[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Team Members[m
[32m+[m[32mTechnologies Used:[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Python[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Pandas[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● NumPy[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● SQLite[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Power BI[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Jupyter Notebook[m
[32m+[m[32mAcademic Year: 2025– 2026[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExecutive Summary[m
[32m+[m[32mThe Bluestock Mutual Fund Analytics Platform is a comprehensive data[m
[32m+[m[32manalytics solution developed to analyze mutual fund performance, investor[m
[32m+[m[32mbehavior, industry trends, and portfolio risk. The project combines data[m
[32m+[m[32mengineering, exploratory data analysis, performance measurement, advanced[m
[32m+[m[32mrisk analytics, and dashboard visualization into a single integrated platform.[m
[32m+[m[32mThe project begins with collecting and cleaning multiple mutual fund datasets.[m
[32m+[m[32mAn ETL pipeline was developed using Python to automate extraction,[m
[32m+[m[32mtransformation, and loading processes. Cleaned data was stored in a SQLite[m
[32m+[m[32mdatabase and analyzed using Python libraries such as Pandas and NumPy.[m
[32m+[m[32mSeveral performance metrics including CAGR, Sharpe Ratio, Sortino Ratio,[m
[32m+[m[32mAlpha, Beta, and Maximum Drawdown were calculated. Advanced analytics[m
[32m+[m[32mtechniques such as Value at Risk (VaR), Conditional Value at Risk (CVaR),[m
[32m+[m[32minvestor cohort analysis, SIP continuity analysis, and portfolio concentration[m
[32m+[m[32manalysis were implemented.[m
[32m+[m[32mAn interactive Power BI dashboard was developed to visualize key insights[m
[32m+[m[32mrelated to industry growth, fund performance, investor behavior, and SIP[m
[32m+[m[32mtrends. The final solution provides investors and analysts with meaningful[m
[32m+[m[32minsights to support informed decision-making.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mProblem Statement and Objectives[m
[32m+[m[32mProblem Statement[m
[32m+[m[32mThe mutual fund industry generates large amounts of data related to fund[m
[32m+[m[32mperformance, investor transactions, assets under management, and portfolio[m
[32m+[m[32mholdings. Investors often struggle to analyze this information effectively and[m
[32m+[m[32midentify suitable investment opportunities.[m
[32m+[m[32mTraditional approaches rely on manual analysis and fragmented reports,[m
[32m+[m[32mmaking it difficult to evaluate risk, compare funds, and understand investor[m
[32m+[m[32mbehavior.[m
[32m+[m[32mObjectives[m
[32m+[m[32mThe primary objectives of this project are:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    1. Build an automated ETL pipeline for mutual fund datasets.[m
[32m+[m[32m    2. Store cleaned data in a structured SQLite database.[m
[32m+[m[32m    3. Perform exploratory data analysis to identify trends and patterns.[m
[32m+[m[32m    4. Calculate important performance metrics.[m
[32m+[m[32m    5. Implement advanced risk analytics techniques.[m
[32m+[m[32m    6. Develop a mutual fund recommendation engine.[m
[32m+[m[32m    7. Create an interactive Power BI dashboard.[m
[32m+[m[32m    8. Generate actionable business insights.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mData Sources[m
[32m+[m[32mThe project uses multiple datasets representing different aspects of the[m
[32m+[m[32mmutual fund ecosystem.[m
[32m+[m[32mFund Master Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32mContains details about mutual fund schemes including:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● AMFI Code[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Scheme Name[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Fund House[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Category[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Plan Type[m
[32m+[m[32mNAV History Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32mContains historical Net Asset Value records used for:[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Return calculations[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Risk calculations[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Performance comparisons[m
[32m+[m[32mAUM Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32mContains assets under management information for different fund houses.[m
[32m+[m[32mSIP Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32mContains monthly SIP inflow information used to analyze investor[m
[32m+[m[32mparticipation and industry growth.[m
[32m+[m[32mInvestor Transaction Dataset[m
[32m+[m[32mContains:[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Investor ID[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Transaction Type[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Transaction Date[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Investment Amount[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Demographic Information[m
[32m+[m[32mThese datasets collectively provide a complete view of the mutual fund[m
[32m+[m[32mecosystem.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mETL Pipeline Design[m
[32m+[m[32mOverview[m
[32m+[m[32mETL stands for Extract, Transform, and Load.[m
[32m+[m[32mThe ETL pipeline was developed to automate data preparation and ensure data[m
[32m+[m[32mquality before analysis.[m
[32m+[m[32mExtraction Phase[m
[32m+[m[32mRaw CSV files were collected from different sources and loaded into Python[m
[32m+[m[32musing Pandas.[m
[32m+[m[32mKey Activities:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Reading CSV files[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Validating schema[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Checking data completeness[m
[32m+[m[32mTransformation Phase[m
[32m+[m[32mData cleaning operations included:[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Missing value handling[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Data type conversion[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Standardization[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Duplicate removal[m
[32m+[m[32mThese steps improved data consistency and reliability.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mETL Pipeline Design (Continued)[m
[32m+[m[32mLoading Phase[m
[32m+[m[32mAfter transformation, cleaned datasets were stored in:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Processed CSV files[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● SQLite Database[m
[32m+[m[32mBenefits of ETL Pipeline[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    1. Improved data quality[m
[32m+[m[32m    2. Reduced manual effort[m
[32m+[m[32m    3. Faster analytics[m
[32m+[m[32m    4. Consistent reporting[m
[32m+[m[32mScripts Developed[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● data_ingestion.py[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● clean_transactions.py[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● load_sqlite.py[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● validate_amfi.py[m
[32m+[m[32mThe ETL process forms the foundation for all subsequent analytics activities.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mDatabase Design[m
[32m+[m[32mSQLite was used as the central storage layer for the project.[m
[32m+[m[32mMain Tables[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    1. fund_master[m
[32m+[m[32m    2. nav_history[m
[32m+[m[32m    3. scheme_performance[m
[32m+[m[32m    4. investor_transactions[m
[32m+[m[32m    5. benchmark_indices[m
[32m+[m[32mRelationships[m
[32m+[m[32mAMFI Code was used as the primary linking field between tables.[m
[32m+[m[32mBenefits of using SQLite:[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Lightweight[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Easy integration with Python[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Portable database file[m
[32m+[m[32m    ● Fast querying for analytics[m
[32m+[m[32mThe database structure enabled efficient retrieval of information required[m
[32m+[m[32mfor performance and risk analysis.[m
[32m+[m
